<p>
I made this for a dinner party recently... it was a tremendous hit!  I, too, couldn&#39;t find a recipe for the right kind of cassata cake (the ones from my childhood were from Catalano&#39;s in Highland Heights)-- this was amazing.<br /><br />The outside of the cassata cakes I remember were covered in sheets of white chocolate; I couldn&#39;t re-create that in my kitchen, so I just took a vegetable peeler to a white chocolate baking bar and covered the top of the cake with white chocolate curls.
